                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/614: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marriner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-04T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 4, 1933—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. For Norman Davis. For your information, the discussions now under way here
                    with the British representatives are already turning in the direction of your
                    second alternative.<note n="36" xml:id="d357fn36">See telegram No. 71, April 3,
                        from the Chargé in Great Britain, <ref target="#pg_482">p. 482</ref>.</note>
                    The British Ambassador and I have already tentatively agreed to invite from time
                    to time representatives of other nations to join informally in our current
                    discussions of world economic questions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
